section.section:
An applicant for certification as an advanced practice nurse shall:
Be a registered nurse;
Complete an education program approved by the Board;
Submit to the Board:
A completed application for certification as a nurse practitioner, nurse anesthetist, nurse midwife, nurse psychotherapist, or clinical nurse specialist for each area in which certification is sought;
Documentation of an active license in good standing as a registered nurse in the State;
Documentation that the applicant has graduated from an accredited program for advanced practice nursing for nurse practitioners, nurse anesthetists, nurse midwives, nurse psychotherapists, or clinical nurse specialists; and
Documentation of certification as a nurse practitioner, nurse anesthetist, nurse midwife, nurse psychotherapist, or clinical nurse specialist by a nationally recognized certifying body approved by the Board; and
Meet any other requirements that the Board sets.
